        {
          "@type": "Review",
          "itemReviewed": {
            "@type": "School",
            "name": "Prime Academy - Marol Bazar Road"
          },
          "author": {
            "@type": "Person",
            "name": "Vipin Varghese"
          },
          "datePublished": "2021-06-06",
          "reviewRating": {
            "@type": "Rating",
            "ratingValue": "5",
            "bestRating": "5",
            "worstRating": "1"
          },
          "reviewBody": "Undoubtedly one of the best schools in Mumbai. I am talking from personal experience; my daughter has been studying here since Jr. Kg. and never had any complaints. Do not agree with many of the reviews written by other parents. Its not a government aided school, but a well maintained private school. The fees charged is just a cost of maintaining better standards and facilities. So yes it might look a bit expensive but the facilities are worth every penny. The infrastructure, the location, the attention to sports and extracurricular activities along with top class education defines this school.\nThe teachers are quite knowledgeable and well trained. In all aspects whether in academics or sports or cultural events,  they have earned their reputation. They are well managed and skilled in all their abilities. The staff is cooperative too. The best part about the school is that the Director and Principal are very approachable and open to discussions. I recommend this school to all parents looking for a second home for their kids.",
          "publisher": {
            "@type": "Organization",
            "name": "Yellow Slate"
          }
        },
        {
          "@type": "Review",
          "itemReviewed": {
            "@type": "School",
            "name": "Prime Academy - Marol Bazar Road"
          },
          "author": {
            "@type": "Person",
            "name": "Chitra Bharath"
          },
          "datePublished": "2021-06-06",
          "reviewRating": {
            "@type": "Rating",
            "ratingValue": "5",
            "bestRating": "5",
            "worstRating": "1"
          },
          "reviewBody": "Prime Academy is a lovely place for kids, more like a second home and a school I strongly recommend 👍🏼.\nIt provides a very enriching all round learning experience for children, which they will treasure all their lives.\nThe Principal Ms Rehana Kazi,  Director Chaula Joshi and teaching staff are very approachable and open with parents.  My son studied there right from kindergarten to X standard till last year, and has been  very happy. As a parent, I too have a nice and memorable experience with the school . Every school has its own issues and any student/ parent may have issues as well , but the school has always helped us sort them all out in an amicable way .",
          "publisher": {
            "@type": "Organization",
            "name": "Yellow Slate"
          }
        }
